How can custom attributes be added to a field in either the Model or View?

My current solution is to attach the attributes to the model_form Meta. It works, but is not ideal.
When in the Jinja2 template, it would convenient to have the custom attributes accessible directly on each field. In my current solution, I have to do a look up on the form meta.

``` python
class Tasks(Document):
    task = StringField()
    completed = BooleanField(default=False)


class TasksView(FlaskView):
    form = model_form(Tasks)

    def index(self)
         form =  self.form(request.form,
                                  meta={'fields':[
                                            {'id':'completed','width':20, 'height':20},
                                            {'id':'task','width':80,'color':'purple'}
                                        ]
                                  })
         # do other stuff here
        return render_template("my_template.html", form=form)
```

_Note  for context: 
 I'm using the form object to not only render a form, but also in rendering a javascript grid, and other structures where custom attributes defined in Model or View would be convenient to have._

I had a quick question regarding the open_sessions method in `MongoEngineSessionInterface`:

```
def open_session(self, app, request):
    sid = request.cookies.get(app.session_cookie_name)
    if sid:
        stored_session = self.cls.objects(sid=sid).first()

        if stored_session:
            expiration = stored_session.expiration

            if not expiration.tzinfo:
                expiration = expiration.replace(tzinfo=utc)

            if expiration > datetime.datetime.utcnow().replace(tzinfo=utc):
                return MongoEngineSession(initial=stored_session.data, sid=stored_session.sid)

    return MongoEngineSession(sid=str(uuid.uuid4()))
```

It looks to me like the following is true:

If the stored session exists, but it it expired, a new session with a new SID will be created. The old stored session will continue to exist in the database, undeleted.

Is this supposed to be the case?
